Tarisland
Privacy Policy
Last Updated:
9
October
2024
Thank
you
for using our products and services! We respect your concerns about privacy and appreciate your trust and confidence in us.
Please note that this privacy policy (“Privacy Policy”) applies to
the official game version and the Cloud version of Tarisland (“
Game”),
the main website for the Game (“Website”) and webpages for
displaying score and ranking for the Game (“Taris Ranking”), for the Twitch Drops Event and for the Top-Up Rebates Event
(the Game, the Website, Taris Ranking, the Twitch Drops Event and the Top-Up Rebates Event together comprise the “Game Services”)
. If you use any other products or services,
please refer to the privacy policy for that particular product or service
.
If you have any questions about anything in this Privacy Policy, or want to exercise any rights you may have, our contact information can be found
here
.
For the purpose of data protection laws
,
the data controller of your personal information in relation to the Game Services is Proxima Beta Pte. Ltd
.
SUMMARY
Here is a summary of the information contained in this Privacy Policy. You can find more detail by clicking ‘
More Information
’.
What information do we need to be able to provide the Game Services?
In relation to the Game:
·
If you register an account to use the Game then we will need some information from you to set this up. This includes your username, email address, and phone number. We will generate an Open ID, which is an internal ID for your account.
·
If you choose to set up your profile using a social media account, we collect information provided by your social media account service provider to automatically generate your profile, including name and contact email.
·
If you choose to use the Cloud version of the Game, we will collect additional information from you for the purposes of providing this service.
·
To maintain the smooth operation of the Game (which includes activities such as from addressing bugs or malicious activity through to improving functionality), we will process customary device and network information (such as IP address, connection information, device specifications, as well as app- and OS-generated identifiers).
·
If you wish to participate in our surveys, we will process survey information and device data, such as email address, geographic (country or region) location, IP address and browser version, with your consent to
better understand our users and to improve the Game.
·
If you need to get in touch with us, we will retain some information (such as your player identity information, device information and interactions with our help services) so that we can
review and respond to
your concerns.
In relation to the Website:
·
If you register
to receive updates on the development of the Game, and participate in promotional activities (e.g. the raffle feature,
Dragon Raid Bounty and Official launch server first kill), on the Website,
then you will need to register for the LEVEL INFINITE PASS, for which you would need to provide your user name, email address, phone number, and country of residence.
·
To maintain the smooth operation of the Website and
perform statistics on page view and user view of the Website
, we will process customary device and network information (such as IP address).
·
If you access other features on the website, e.g. the
promotional activities
or the questionnaire or the Guild Zone, we may process additional information to provide you with the feature.
In relation to Taris Ranking:
·
If you log in to your Game account or social media account to use Taris Ranking, we collect information provided by your social media account service provider, including name and contact email, to connect to your profile.
·
To maintain operation of Taris Ranking, we will process your profile information, leaderboard highlights, game statistics, and performance data (such as your score and ranking within the Game).
In relation to the Twitch Drops Event:
·
For you to participate in the
Twitch Drops Event
, we would require you to log in to your Twitch account and your LEVEL INFINITE PASS, where we collect information provided by your social media account service provider, including name
and
user ID from Twitch
and open ID from LEVEL INFINITE PASS, to connect to your profile
·
We will process your list of characters for the Game after you log in to your Twitch account and your LEVEL INFINITE PASS account, to provide your Twitch Drops rewards to your chosen character.
In relation to the Top-up Rebates Event:
·
To participate in the Top-Up Rebates Event, we would require
you to log in to your Game account or social media account, we collect information provided by your social media account service provider, including name and user ID and open ID, to connect to your profile.
·
We will process your top-up and transaction details after you log in to your Game account or social media account to determine your rebates amount and items unlocked.
More Information
.
How will we use your information?
·
In relation to the Game
:
We use your information to set up your account, enable you to use the Game, customize your Game experience, enable interaction between users of the Game, save your progress, ensure the safe and secure operation of the Game, address bugs, optimise and improve the Game, protect users, resolve user queries, and allow us to get in touch with you.
·
In relation to the Website:
We use your information to enable you to participate in promotional activities for the Game on the Website, optimise and improve the Website, resolve user queries, provide you with updates of
the Game, and provide you with Guild functions
.
·
In relation to Taris Ranking:
We use your information to enable you to use Taris Ranking, provide you and other players with your score and profile, character information, your in-Game battle records (such as date and duration), zone information, and performance rankings.
·
In relation to the Twitch Drops Event:
We use your information to enable you to participate in the Twitch Drops Event to claim Twitch Drops rewards.
·
In relation to the Top-Up Rebates Event:
We use your information to enable you to participate in the Top-Up Rebates Event so that you can claim rebates as you top-up.
·
We also use your information
to comply with our legal obligations and enforce our legal rights.
More Information
.
Who do we share your information with?
·
We use third parties and work with our affiliates to help us deliver the best possible experience (such as for data analytics purposes as well as for facilitating purchases / in-
G
ame transactions, and customer support).
·
All third party service providers providing services for us are prohibited from retaining, using, or disclosing your personal information for any purpose except where strictly necessary for the Game Services (i.e., to fulfil the purpose(s) described above).
·
In some cases we may be required by a court or be under a legal obligation (such as a valid search warrant or subpoena) to disclose certain information.
More Information
.
Where do we process your information?
·
Pursuant to our contract with you, we may transfer data outside of the location in which you are based for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy.
·
We have servers for the Game Services in Singapore, the United States
, Brazil and Germany
, which can be chosen by you. We also have support, engineering and other teams who may support the Game Services, including from Singapore, Hong Kong and the PRC.
·
For EEA/UK users, transfers between our affiliates and to third parties use applicable safeguards, such as incorporating standard contractual clauses, obtaining your consent first or taking into account adequacy assessments.
More Information
.
How long do we keep your information?
·
Unless otherwise required or permissible by applicable laws, we retain your information for the period during which you maintain an account for the Game, or for so long as the information is needed to fulfil the purpose for which it was collected (as further described in this Privacy Policy). We then delete or anonymise such data, in accordance with applicable laws.
More Information
.
How can I exercise my rights over my information?
·
Certain jurisdictions offer users specific rights with respect to their information, so you may have a right to access or receive a copy of your data, or to delete your data or restrict or object to our processing of your data.
More Information
.
How will we notify you of changes?
·
Changes to this Privacy Policy will be posted here. We will also notify you of changes in accordance with relevant legal requirements.
More Information
.
